<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><span
lang=3DEN style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'>This
apps main task is to allow you to visualise the energy usage that has been
recorded into a comma separated value (csv) file. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><span
lang=3DEN-US style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<h2 style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;page-break-aft=
er:
avoid'><b><u><span lang=3DEN-US style=3D'font-size:14.0pt;mso-ansi-language=
:EN-US'>How
it works.<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></h2>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><span
lang=3DEN-US style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>=A0</span></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'>Open
the app and you will have the following GUI.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter style=3D'text-align:center'><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"_x0000_i1040" =
type=3D"#_x0000_t75"
 style=3D'width:275pt;height:131.5pt;visibility:visible;mso-wrap-style:squa=
re'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"Help_files/image003.png" o:title=3D""/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D367 height=3D175
src=3D"Help_files/image004.jpg" v:shapes=3D"_x0000_i1040"><![endif]></span>=
</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter style=3D'text-align:center'><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'>Buttons
and other UI Controls will appear or disappear depending on the choices you
make as you work with the app. There are two tabs one for charts and one for
Costs. Cost is where we enter the cost of the energy, we will see later that
this is saved to a <span class=3DSpellE>json</span> file. The charts tab ge=
ts its
data from Comms Separated Files (.csv).</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><b><u>Data
Usage<o:p></o:p></u></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><u>CSV
Data Files<o:p></o:p></u></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'>The
folder structure where the data is stored and how it is named is important.=
 The
app starts to look under the folder Data into subfolders for the year, then
under the year into subfolders for the months (Sentence case for months). U=
nder
the months are folders for daily and <span class=3DSpellE>halfhourly</span>=
. This
is illustrated below: </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"_x0000_i1039" =
type=3D"#_x0000_t75"
 style=3D'width:137.5pt;height:175pt;visibility:visible;mso-wrap-style:squa=
re'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"Help_files/image005.png" o:title=3D""/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D183 height=3D233
src=3D"Help_files/image006.jpg" v:shapes=3D"_x0000_i1039"><![endif]></span>=
</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'>The
CSV file name explains what meter it belongs to e.g. </p>

<ul style=3D'margin-top:0cm' type=3Ddisc>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideog=
raph;
     mso-list:l4 level1 lfo3'>ChurchE.csv is the Electric meter for the chu=
rch.
     </li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideog=
raph;
     mso-list:l4 level1 lfo3'>PresbyteryG.csv is the gas meter for the
     presbytery.</li>
</ul>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'>There
are two types of data that can be charted, the half hourly energy usage and=
 the
daily usage. The layout of the csv file is shown below:</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideogra=
ph'><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

